<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFFBFF92FEB1F88FFAFF50E2" blockId="14.[192,1440,1793,1927]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFFBFF92FEB1F88FFE6B5025" box="[256,422,1830,1856]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">COSTA RICA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFFBFF92FE02F88FFDB35025" box="[435,638,1830,1856]" country="Costa Rica" name="Alajuela" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Alajuela Province</collectingRegion>
, San Ramón; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFFBFF92FC93F88FFC395025" box="[802,1012,1830,1856]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" value="2017-09-01">1 September 2017</date>
; Y. Villalobos. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFBFF92FB5BF88EFED05001" authority="(Clerck)" baseAuthorityName="Clerck" baseAuthorityYear="1757" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Misumena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vatia">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFBFF92FB5BF88EFA6D5025" box="[1258,1440,1831,1856]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Misumena vatia</emphasis>
(Clerck)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFBFF92FE9FF8E0FE755001" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1833" box="[302,440,1865,1892]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Thomisidae</taxonomicName>
). The wasp stood near the paralyzed crab spider as it laid, ventral side upward, on the ground (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFBFF92FE91F8C5FE1850E3" author="Villalobos Y." box="[288,469,1900,1926]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" refId="ref27294" refString="Villalobos Y. 2017. Spider Wasps (Family Pompilidae). Available at https: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 7761830. (Last accessed 17 January 2021)." type="url" year="2017">Villalobos 2017</bibRefCitation>
). This host record is listed as 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFBFF92FCA9F8C5FC2350E2" box="[792,1006,1900,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Poecilopompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFBFF92FCA9F8C5FC0450E3" box="[792,969,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Poecilopompilus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFBFF92FBA0F8C5FAE350E2" author="Kurczewski FE &amp; West RC &amp; Waichert C &amp; Kissane KC &amp; Ubick D &amp; Pitts JP" box="[1041,1326,1900,1927]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref25112" refString="Kurczewski FE, West RC, Waichert C, Kissane KC, Ubick D, Pitts JP. 2020 b. New and unusual host records for North American and South American spider wasps (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Zootaxa 4891: 1 - 112." type="journal article" year="2020">Kurczewski et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFFAFF93FEB1FF7FFE5F5618" blockId="15.[191,1441,214,767]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFFAFF93FEB1FF7FFE685795" box="[256,421,214,240]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">COSTA RICA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFFAFF93FE00FF7FFDB75795" box="[433,634,214,240]" country="Costa Rica" name="Alajuela" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Alajuela Province</collectingRegion>
, San Ramón, Soltis Center; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFFAFF93FC0FFF7FFBFC5795" box="[958,1073,214,240]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="2018-05">May 2018</date>
; S. Marshall. Host: Unidentified species (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FEAEFF50FE655671" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1833" box="[287,424,249,276]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Thomisidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. A photograph shows a wasp standing near the paralyzed crab spider as it laid, ventral side upward, on a leaf above the ground 
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFAFF93FCC8FEB5FC4F5653" box="[889,898,284,310]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">(</emphasis>
Marshall, University of Guelph, Guelph, Ontario, Canada, 2020 pers. comm.; Pitts, 2020 pers. comm.). This host record is listed as 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FBFFFE96FAEE563F" box="[1102,1315,319,346]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Poecilopompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFAFF93FBFFFE96FB32563C" box="[1102,1279,319,345]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Poecilopompilus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFAFF93FAF9FEE9FE435618" author="Kurczewski FE &amp; West RC &amp; Waichert C &amp; Kissane KC &amp; Ubick D &amp; Pitts JP" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref25112" refString="Kurczewski FE, West RC, Waichert C, Kissane KC, Ubick D, Pitts JP. 2020 b. New and unusual host records for North American and South American spider wasps (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Zootaxa 4891: 1 - 112." type="journal article" year="2020">Kurczewski et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFFAFF93FEB1FE2CFECB556C" blockId="15.[191,1441,214,767]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFFAFF93FEB1FE2CFDE356FA" box="[256,558,389,415]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">DOMINICAN REPUBLIC</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFFAFF93FD86FE2CFD3756FA" box="[567,762,389,415]" country="Dominican Republic" name="Distrito Nacional" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Distrito Nacional</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFFAFF93FCB2FE2CFC7856FA" box="[771,949,389,415]" country="Dominican Republic" name="Santo Domingo" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Santo Domingo</collectingRegion>
; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFFAFF93FC0FFE2CFB5C56FA" box="[958,1169,389,415]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="2021-11-27">27 November 2021</date>
, 1717 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFFAFF93FB67FE2CFADD56FA" box="[1238,1296,389,415]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/tba0-w5ye" name="University of Tennessee at Chattanooga" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="University or college">UTC</collectionCode>
; F. Paz. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FF0EFE01FEFA56A7" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[191,311,424,450]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Mecaphesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFAFF93FF0EFE01FEFA56A7" box="[191,311,424,450]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Mecaphesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
? 
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFAFF93FEFBFE01FE7056A7" box="[330,445,424,450]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">californica</emphasis>
(Banks), adult or subadult female (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FCF8FE01FC1E56A6" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1833" box="[841,979,424,451]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Thomisidae</taxonomicName>
). The wasp stood on a leaf and examined the immobilized crab spider which was cached, dorsal side upward, in the axil of the opposite leaf stem (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFAFF93FAC6FE65FF37556C" author="Paz F." pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref25961" refString="Paz F. 2021. Genus Poecilopompilus. Available at https: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 102654691. (Last accessed 7 December 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Paz 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFFAFF93FEB1FDBBFD315516" blockId="15.[191,1441,214,767]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFFAFF93FEB1FDBBFE835549" box="[256,334,530,556]" name="Haiti" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">HAITI</collectingCountry>
, Port-au-Prince Arrondissement, Kenscoff; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFFAFF93FC82FDBBFC2A5548" box="[819,999,530,557]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="2015-01-11">11 January 2015</date>
; 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFFAFF93FC40FDBBFBCB5549" box="[1009,1030,530,556]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">R</collectionCode>
. Durocher. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FB77FDBAFA905549" box="[1222,1373,530,556]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Metazygia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFAFF93FB77FDBAFAF55549" box="[1222,1336,531,556]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Metazygia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FADBFDBBFEC35535" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Araneidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. The immobilized orb-weaver laid on its left side on vegetation while the wasp, with raised wings, stood beside it (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFAFF93FDF1FDF1FD3D5516" author="Durocher R." box="[576,752,600,627]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref22967" refString="Durocher R. 2015. Pompilidae Poecilopompilus vs Metazygia. Available at https: // facebook. com / photo. php? fbid = 101526718 00816589 &amp; id = 534406588 &amp; set = a. 10153890802541589. (Last accessed 25 January 2021)." type="url" year="2015">Durocher 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFFAFF93FEB1FDD5FB66559A" blockId="15.[191,1441,214,767]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<materialsCitation id="3B6B3C9BFFFAFF93FEB1FDD5FB6655F0" box="[256,1195,635,662]" country="Peru" location="Coche Cashu Biological Station" municipality="Manu National Park" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Cusco">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFFAFF93FEB1FDD5FE8555F3" box="[256,328,636,662]" name="Peru" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">PERU</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFFAFF93FEE7FDD2FE5155F0" box="[342,412,635,661]" country="Peru" name="Cusco" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Cusco</collectingRegion>
Department, 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BD8ACBCFFFAFF93FDF1FDD5FCE355F0" box="[576,814,635,662]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Manu National Park</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<location id="8EDC601DFFFAFF93FC8CFDD2FB6655F0" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AA87D0FFFBFF93FF71F8A8FB66559A:8EDC601DFFFAFF93FC8CFDD2FB6655F0" box="[829,1195,635,661]" country="Peru" municipality="Manu National Park" name="Coche Cashu Biological Station" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" stateProvince="Cusco">Coche Cashu Biological Station</location>
</materialsCitation>
; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFFAFF93FB0BFDD2FAB255F0" box="[1210,1407,635,662]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="2021-10-25">25 October 2021</date>
; P. Bertner. Host: Unidentified species (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFAFF93FDE8FD37FD0655DC" authorityName="Blackwall" authorityYear="1841" box="[601,715,670,697]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Salticidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult species. The wasp straddled the immobilized jumping spider, ventral side upward, and grasped its spinnerets with her mandibles. She amputated all but the prey’s hindlegs at the coxa-trochanter joints to facilitate forward transport (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFAFF93FBB6FD4CFB52559A" author="Bertner P." box="[1031,1183,741,767]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref21399" refString="Bertner P. 2021. Spider wasp (Pompilidae) with jumping spider prey. Available at https: // www. flickr. com / photos / rainforests / 51663333057 / in / album- 72157625475420352 /. (Last accessed 15 December 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Bertner 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
